# OpenClaw — the one shared local-LLM model alias for all of my apps.
#
# Apps never name a raw Ollama model (qwen3.5:4b, etc.) directly. They all ask
# for "openclaw", and this file decides what that actually is. Swap the FROM
# line, re-run ./install.sh, and every app moves together — with one copy of the
# weights resident in RAM instead of each app loading its own.
#
# Current pick: qwen3:4b (Q4_K_M). Reasoning model — callers should send
# "think": false per-request (Ollama has no Modelfile-level switch yet; see
# FOR-AGENTS.md).
#
# WHY num_gpu (2026-07-04): this Jetson's CUDA/ggml build fails any *single*
# cudaMalloc larger than ~1.9 GiB, even with 5+ GiB reported free (it's an
# allocator limit, NOT out-of-memory — not fixable with more RAM/CMA). A full
# 36-layer offload of qwen3:4b needs one ~2.3 GiB weight buffer and OOMs.
# Capping GPU layers keeps that single buffer under the limit; the remaining
# layers run on CPU. 24/36 measured to load; tune up toward the ceiling for
# more speed, down if a load OOMs.
#
# NOTE: failed loads leak GPU memory that only a *reboot* clears (a service
# restart is not enough). If loads start OOMing after a bad attempt, reboot.
FROM qwen3:4b

# Qwen3 non-thinking sampling params.
PARAMETER temperature 0.7
PARAMETER top_p 0.8
PARAMETER top_k 20
PARAMETER min_p 0

# Cap GPU layers so the single weight buffer stays under the ~1.9 GiB
# cudaMalloc ceiling; rest run on CPU. See WHY above.
PARAMETER num_gpu 24

# Match the server runtime (-c 4096). Keep callers' prompt theirs.
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096
